bib_record.title: Study of the 14N(d,d)14N and 14N(d,p)15N angular distributions and excited states of 15N

free_txt: The reaction products were detected by means
of surface barrier counters of 50 mm2 area and about
700 mu-m deep; the detector resolution was 40 keV.
Digitizing error
Digitizing error
The uncertainties include errors due to
(i) the measurement of the beam integrator current,
approx. 0.5 %;
(ii) the pressure in the scattering chamber, approx.
2%, but more for low-pressure measurements;
(iii) the analysis of spectra, and
(iv) the contamination by background peaks,
especially those from the 160 + d reaction.
The errors due to the analysis of the groups P4-P6 are
smaller than the statistical errors since very dry
nitrogen and good-resolution detectors were used.
For the deuteron and P7 groups, the large background
introduces an additional error which in some cases is
greater than the statistical error. The errors at
forward angles are also large because of the very
strong elastic scattering peak; to avoid pile-up,
a 10 nA beam was used.
The gas target was composed of natural nitrogen
(99% 14N) and was free of water vapour. The pressure
of the gas in the chamber was fixed at 2 or 10 mm of
Hg to secure a complete separation of the alpha and
proton groups at all angles.
